### **🔒 Privacy & Security Comparison Across Social Networks**  

| **Platform**  | **End-to-End Encryption (E2EE)** | **Data Collection Practices** | **User Control Over Data** | **Security Features** | **AI in Privacy & Security** | **Regulatory Compliance (GDPR, CCPA, etc.)** |  
|--------------|--------------------------------|----------------------------|------------------------|-------------------|--------------------------|--------------------------------------|  
| **Facebook (Meta)**  | ❌ (Only in Messenger secret chats) | ✅ Extensive data tracking & targeted ads | 🟡 Some control via settings | ✅ 2FA, login alerts, security checks | ✅ AI for fraud & content moderation | ✅ Complies with GDPR but has faced violations |  
| **Twitter (X)**  | ❌ No E2EE for DMs | ✅ Collects user data for ads & engagement | 🟡 Some data settings available | ✅ 2FA, security alerts | ✅ AI for spam/fraud detection | ✅ Complies with GDPR but has been criticized |  
| **Google**  | 🟡 E2EE for some services (Gmail, Meet) | ✅ Heavy data collection for ads & services | 🟡 Limited data deletion control | ✅ Strong account security tools | ✅ AI for phishing & account protection | ✅ GDPR-compliant but fined multiple times |  
| **Telegram**  | ✅ E2EE in "Secret Chats" only | 🟡 Less tracking but stores metadata | 🟡 Limited user control | ✅ Strong encryption, self-destructing messages | 🟡 AI for spam filtering | ✅ GDPR-compliant but criticized for lack of transparency |  
| **WhatsApp**  | ✅ Full E2EE for all messages | 🟡 Metadata collection (who you talk to, when) | 🟡 Limited control over metadata | ✅ 2FA, self-destructing messages | ✅ AI for spam & scam filtering | ✅ GDPR-compliant but criticized for data sharing with Meta |  
| **Instagram**  | ❌ No E2EE for DMs | ✅ High data collection for ad targeting | 🟡 Some user control via settings | ✅ 2FA, suspicious login alerts | ✅ AI for moderation & fraud detection | ✅ Complies with GDPR but fined for privacy issues |  
| **Slack**  | ❌ No E2EE for messages | 🟡 Collects workspace data but less than social platforms | ✅ Enterprise-level controls | ✅ Enterprise security, 2FA, SSO | ✅ AI for monitoring security risks | ✅ GDPR & enterprise compliance |  
| **Viber**  | ✅ Full E2EE for 1:1 and group chats | 🟡 Minimal tracking compared to Meta platforms | 🟡 Some data deletion options | ✅ Strong encryption, security alerts | 🟡 Limited AI in security | ✅ GDPR-compliant with strong encryption focus |  
| **LinkedIn**  | ❌ No E2EE for messages | ✅ Extensive data tracking for ads & networking | 🟡 Limited control over visibility & data | ✅ 2FA, security alerts | ✅ AI for fake profile detection & moderation | ✅ GDPR-compliant but criticized for aggressive tracking |  
| **TikTok**  | ❌ No E2EE for messages | ✅ Extensive data collection, biometric tracking concerns | 🟡 Limited control over algorithmic tracking | 🟡 Basic security settings, 2FA | ✅ AI for content moderation & security | 🟡 GDPR compliance debated, scrutiny over China ties |  

---

### **🔍 Key Privacy & Security Takeaways**  

- **Best for End-to-End Encryption (E2EE):** **WhatsApp, Viber, Telegram (Secret Chats only)**  
- **Most Aggressive Data Collection:** **Facebook, Google, TikTok, LinkedIn**  
- **Best User Control Over Data:** **Google (partially), Slack (enterprise-level)**  
- **AI in Security & Moderation:** **Google, Meta (Facebook, Instagram, WhatsApp), LinkedIn**  
- **Most Regulatory Scrutiny:** **Facebook, Google, TikTok**  

💡 **Trend:** Privacy regulations (GDPR, CCPA) continue to **shape social media policies**, but **AI-driven data collection & security remain a double-edged sword.**  
